Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:03.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我生来便是英格兰的郡长\N{\rEnglish}(U HTRED) I was born an ealdorman of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.76,0:00:07.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德，贝班堡乌特雷德之子，欢迎来到基督的世界\N{\rEnglish}Uhtred, son of Uhtred of Bebbanburg, welcome to the Christian world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.08,0:00:10.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}诺森布里亚贝班堡领地的继承人\N{\rEnglish}Heir to the Northumbrian lands of Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:12.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你带琥珀石了吗?         - 带了\N{\rEnglish}- You have your stone, amber? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.04,0:00:17.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这片土地是我们的祖先打下来的，必要时你得为它而死\N{\rEnglish}Our ancestors took this land and you will die for it if needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.80,0:00:20.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我第一次上战场时才十二岁\N{\rEnglish}I was 12 years old when I Hrst went to war.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.72,0:00:22.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}杀光他们！\N{\rEnglish}(LORD UHTRED) Kill them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.52,0:00:24.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我亲眼看着父亲战死\N{\rEnglish}I saw my father killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.40,0:00:25.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我叔父夺了我的领地,\N{\rEnglish}My uncle took my lands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:28.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还向丹麦人俯首称臣\N{\rEnglish}and pledged his allegiance to the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.24,0:00:32.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我劝你一句，别惹乌巴,\N{\rEnglish}My advice for you is to never cross Ubba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.80,0:00:34.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}永远别跟他动手\N{\rEnglish}and never, never fight him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.80,0:00:38.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我和撒克逊女孩布丽达被入侵者掳走\N{\rEnglish}Stolen by the invaders, along with the Saxon girl Brida,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.68,0:00:42.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我先做了奴隶，后来成了拉格纳伯爵的养子\N{\rEnglish}I became Hrst a slave and then a son to Earl Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.60,0:00:44.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那就是我的家，我的人生\N{\rEnglish}That was my family. My life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.68,0:00:47.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}小拉格纳，我的兄弟，还有布丽达，我的爱人\N{\rEnglish}Young Ragnar, my brothen and Brida, my lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.60,0:00:49.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}命运让我成了一个丹麦人\N{\rEnglish}Fate had made me a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.80,0:00:52.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}然后命运带来了背叛\N{\rEnglish}And then fate brought betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.12,0:00:55.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.48,0:01:00.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我不会袖手旁观，让属于我的东西被人夺走\N{\rEnglish}I will not stand by and have everything taken from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.68,0:01:03.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝班堡是我的!\N{\rEnglish}Bebbanburg's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.24,0:01:05.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}命运主宰一切\N{\rEnglish}Destiny is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.64,0:01:06.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}备马\N{\rEnglish}Horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.16,0:01:59.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}往树林跑\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) Head for the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.16,0:02:13.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.56,0:02:19.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}往右, 那道山脊后面有条沟\N{\rEnglish}Go right. There's a gully over that ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.68,0:02:42.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}找马蹄印，一定会留下马蹄印\N{\rEnglish}(AELFRIC) Hoof-marks. There must be hoof-marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.80,0:02:45.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}附近一定有马蹄印\N{\rEnglish}There must be hoof-marks somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.36,0:02:49.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}再去叫些人来，我要找到他\N{\rEnglish}Fetch more men, I want him found.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.76,0:02:53.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就算追到麦西亚也要找到他\N{\rEnglish}We'll go as far as Mercia if need be, but I want him found
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.80,0:02:55.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我要他死\N{\rEnglish}and I want him dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.56,0:02:59.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他长得像我父亲\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) Looked like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.32,0:03:01.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他知道你还活着，会一直找你的      - 让他找去\N{\rEnglish}- He knows you're alive,he'll Keep looking for you. - Let him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.84,0:03:04.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我会杀了他，夺回属于我的一切\N{\rEnglish}I'm going to kill him and take back what's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.80,0:03:07.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他有军队，还有丹麦人撑腰\N{\rEnglish}He has an army, choice of the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.16,0:03:08.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你只有我一个人     - 不\N{\rEnglish}- All you have is me. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.60,0:03:11.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们还有乌巴\N{\rEnglish}We have Ubba.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.48,0:03:13.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们去找他，把实情告诉他\N{\rEnglish}We go to him with our story
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.32,0:03:15.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}借他的军队，为拉格纳报仇\N{\rEnglish}and with his army, we avenge Ragnar's death
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.04,0:03:17.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}然后夺回贝班堡\N{\rEnglish}and we take back Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.08,0:03:21.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 就这么简单?      - 对\N{\rEnglish}- It's that simple? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:25.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就是这样\N{\rEnglish}Yes. Tsk, tsk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.72,0:03:48.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}布丽达\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) Brida.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.96,0:03:52.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}布丽达\N{\rEnglish}Brida.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.36,0:03:54.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}给我唱首歌\N{\rEnglish}Sing me a song.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.88,0:03:57.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不唱，我又不是你的吟游诗人\N{\rEnglish}I won't, and I'm not your skald.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.20,0:03:59.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}说得对，再说你唱歌能把鸟都吓跑\N{\rEnglish}True, and what's more, you'd frighten the birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.84,0:04:01.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}什么?\N{\rEnglish}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.64,0:04:03.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}空气里有种味道\N{\rEnglish}There's a taste in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.16,0:04:08.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}死亡的气息\N{\rEnglish}Death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.64,0:05:23.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.68,0:05:38.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.72,0:05:46.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谁干的？谁洗劫了这个村子？\N{\rEnglish}Who did this? Who sacked the village?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.44,0:05:49.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我动不了 - 你的背断了\N{\rEnglish}- (MAN) I cannot move. - Your back is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.60,0:05:51.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.28,0:05:54.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 谁干的？ - 你心里清楚\N{\rEnglish}- Who did it? - You know who did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:05:56.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是丹麦人干的\N{\rEnglish}Danes did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.72,0:05:58.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为什么？\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.84,0:06:01.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为什么丹麦人要袭击一个给他们提供粮食的村子？\N{\rEnglish}Why should the Danes attack a village that feeds them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.80,0:06:03.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}报复\N{\rEnglish}Revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.72,0:06:06.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不过丹麦人杀人需要借口吗？\N{\rEnglish}But since when have Danes need an excuse to kill?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.44,0:06:09.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}报复？报复什么？\N{\rEnglish}(BRIDA) Revenge? Revenge for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:12.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}嗯？\N{\rEnglish}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.28,0:06:15.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}报复什么？说出来，我就给你个痛快\N{\rEnglish}Revenge for what? And I'll end it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.84,0:06:18.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这附近北边有人造反\N{\rEnglish}An uprising north of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.44,0:06:22.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个撒克逊奴隶，在婚宴上杀了自己的主人\N{\rEnglish}A Saxon slave. He killed his master at a wedding party.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.72,0:06:26.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.12,0:06:29.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那个奴隶叫什么名字？\N{\rEnglish}What was the name of this slave?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.76,0:06:33.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 嗯？ - 你一个丹麦人，英语说得不错嘛\N{\rEnglish}- Huh? - You speak English well for a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.88,0:06:35.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他叫什么名字\N{\rEnglish}His name.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.68,0:06:37.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.56,0:06:39.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.48,0:06:48.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}给我个痛快\N{\rEnglish}End it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:51.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.32,0:06:53.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:56.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.04,0:07:05.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 说出来 - 说什么？\N{\rEnglish}- Say it. - (BRIDA) Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.92,0:07:08.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 说你心里想的 - 你脑子里装的是屎\N{\rEnglish}- What you are thinking. - You have a turd
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.48,0:07:11.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 谢谢\N{\rEnglish}- where there's supposed to be a mind. - (LAUGHS) Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.60,0:07:14.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们根本不该去贝班堡\N{\rEnglish}We should never have gone to Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.76,0:07:17.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}应该让他们以为你已经死了\N{\rEnglish}We should have let them believe that you were dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.24,0:07:23.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不，你错了\N{\rEnglish}No, you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.24,0:07:25.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我要让他们知道我还活着\N{\rEnglish}I want them to know that I'm alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.40,0:07:30.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我必须让他们知道我还活着，因为他们占着我的东西\N{\rEnglish}I need them to know that I'm alive because they hold what's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:34.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我感觉好多了 - 是吗?\N{\rEnglish}- I feel better for it. - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.44,0:07:37.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}狗在树旁撒尿也一样爽\N{\rEnglish}So does a dog pissing on a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.12,0:07:40.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你想让我汪汪叫? - 我们该做的\N{\rEnglish}- You wish me to bark? - What we needed to do
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.60,0:07:45.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是南下去找首领乌巴，把拉格纳的死告诉他\N{\rEnglish}was to ride south to the Chieftain Ubba and tell the story of Ragnar's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.44,0:07:48.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 现在去还来得及 - 可现在还有另一个故事\N{\rEnglish}- We'll do it now. - Now, there's a second story
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.24,0:07:52.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 一个奴隶杀死主人的版本 - 乌巴知道拉格纳是我义父\N{\rEnglish}- about a slave who killed his master. - Ubba knows Ragnar was my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.16,0:07:54.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他什么都不知道，我看他早忘了\N{\rEnglish}He knows nothing. I doubt he'll remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.56,0:07:58.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他会相信自己先听到的那个故事，然后杀了你\N{\rEnglish}He will believe the story he hears first and he will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.96,0:08:05.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你要是会写字，就可以写信给他\N{\rEnglish}If you could write, you could write to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:10.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他要是识字的话，呵\N{\rEnglish}If he could read, heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.64,0:08:16.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你让我们没有别的选择\N{\rEnglish}You've left us no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.20,0:08:20.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们必须去找乌巴，然后希望他相信你\N{\rEnglish}We must find Ubba, and hope he believes you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:29.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.60,0:08:33.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.92,0:08:36.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.44,0:08:46.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谢谢\N{\rEnglish}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.32,0:08:52.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝奥卡神父\N{\rEnglish}(MAN) Father Beooca.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.80,0:08:54.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}神父\N{\rEnglish}Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.80,0:08:56.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}赛格沃尔\N{\rEnglish}Segwall.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.32,0:08:59.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我在国王大厅等你\N{\rEnglish}I'll see you in the Kings Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.48,0:09:20.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人?\N{\rEnglish}My lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.32,0:09:25.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德大人，是我，贝奥卡神父\N{\rEnglish}My Lord Alfred, it is I, Father Beocca.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:28.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人，国王召集议事了\N{\rEnglish}My lord, the king has called council.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.52,0:09:31.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}别看着我 神父\N{\rEnglish}(ALFRED) Do not look at me, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.88,0:09:36.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我是个罪人，一个十恶不赦的罪人 - 大人，我们都是罪人\N{\rEnglish}- I am a sinner. I'm a grievous sinner. - We are all sinners, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.92,0:09:39.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而且我已成婚，我本不该娶妻的\N{\rEnglish}And I am married. I should never have married.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.88,0:09:42.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}主降下诱惑来考验我们\N{\rEnglish}He sends temptation to test us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.88,0:09:45.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}当我们堕落，祂便差遣丹麦人来惩罚我们\N{\rEnglish}When we fail, he sends the Danes to punish us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.44,0:09:48.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我本不该成婚，我应该投身教会\N{\rEnglish}I should never have married, I should've joined the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.68,0:09:50.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我应该去修道院的\N{\rEnglish}I should've gone to a monastery.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.60,0:09:52.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}主本能在你身上得到一位忠诚的仆人\N{\rEnglish}God would've found a great servant in you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.92,0:09:55.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我觉得祂另有安排\N{\rEnglish}but I feel he has other plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.56,0:09:58.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}若你兄长有所不测，人们便会转而依仗你\N{\rEnglish}If your brother were to die, it'd be to you people would turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.12,0:10:01.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}哦，求主保佑他平安\N{\rEnglish}Oh, pray God he does not die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.56,0:10:04.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我又能做个什么样的国王呢?\N{\rEnglish}What kind of a king would I be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.84,0:10:07.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人，你将是天主的国王\N{\rEnglish}You will be God's king, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.40,0:10:10.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你已蒙罗马圣父祝福与拣选\N{\rEnglish}You've been blessed and chosen by the Holy Father in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.60,0:10:12.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你将是天主的国王\N{\rEnglish}You would be God's king.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.72,0:10:17.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}-我见过那个折磨着你的女孩了     - 必须将她驱逐\N{\rEnglish}-I have seen the girl who torments you     - Must be banished.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.36,0:10:19.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不，她应该被带来服侍你左右\N{\rEnglish}No, she should be brought into your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:21.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不，我做不到\N{\rEnglish}No. No, I could not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.76,0:10:25.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你要抵挡住她的诱惑，让祂看见你的坚强\N{\rEnglish}You will resist her. You will let him see your strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.68,0:10:28.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你要感谢祂赐下诱惑，再赞美祂\N{\rEnglish}You will thank him for tempting you and then praise him
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.72,0:10:31.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}赞美祂让你抵住了诱惑\N{\rEnglish}for resisting the temptation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.40,0:10:38.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}尽管如此\N{\rEnglish}Notwithstanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.56,0:10:42.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我有一个消息，您或许该带到议会去\N{\rEnglish}I have news you may wish to take to council.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.92,0:10:45.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 什么消息?     - 大人，北方爆发了英格兰人的起义\N{\rEnglish}- What news? - English uprising, lord, in the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.12,0:10:47.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}起义被镇压了\N{\rEnglish}It was defeated,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.84,0:10:51.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但发起这次起义的贵族是贝班堡的乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}but the nobleman responsible was Uhtred of Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.16,0:10:52.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我认识他\N{\rEnglish}I know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:54.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他幼时被丹麦人掳走\N{\rEnglish}He was taken by the Danes as a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.12,0:10:57.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是个虔诚的孩子\N{\rEnglish}a God-fearing child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.24,0:10:59.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 看来他心里依然是个英格兰人       - 他还活着?\N{\rEnglish}- Clearly his heart remains English. - He lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.88,0:11:01.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我相信他还活着\N{\rEnglish}I believe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.72,0:11:06.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他是个勇士，大人     据说他杀了他的丹麦主人和四十个人\N{\rEnglish}He is a warrior, lord. They say he killed his Danish master and 40 men.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.88,0:11:09.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他熟悉丹麦人的方式，会说他们的语言，会是个有用的人\N{\rEnglish}Knows their ways, speaks their language. He'd be useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.08,0:11:13.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 您可以在议会上提到他        - 他为什么要杀自己的主人?\N{\rEnglish}- You could mention him in council. - Why would he kill his master?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.00,0:11:16.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为了仇恨? 为了钱财? 还是为了快意?\N{\rEnglish}For blood? For money? For pleasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.64,0:11:18.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 为了英格兰，大人- 但我们怎么知道?\N{\rEnglish}- For England, lord. - But how do we know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.96,0:11:23.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他很可能只是又一个挥剑四方的异教徒\N{\rEnglish}He may well be just one more pagan with a busy sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.36,0:11:27.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 但我认识他，大人      - 不，贝奥卡神父，你曾经认识他\N{\rEnglish}- But I know him, lord. - No, Father Beocca, you knew him once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.16,0:11:29.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你认识的是那个孩子\N{\rEnglish}You knew him as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.80,0:11:32.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}若蒙天主庇佑，我可以派人到各处打探他的消息\N{\rEnglish}I could send word into the country, God willing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.52,0:11:34.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不过是个虚影，是异教徒口中的传言\N{\rEnglish}He's a ghost. He's a pagan rumour.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.48,0:11:37.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}若他真能现身，或许才值得一提\N{\rEnglish}Should he become flesh and blood, then he may merit a mention.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:41.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我的信仰，只留给天主一人\N{\rEnglish}However, my faith, I reserve for God alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.64,0:11:49.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}眼下关于那个女孩你说得也许没错\N{\rEnglish}Now, about this girl, you may be right about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.72,0:11:51.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让她进入我的直属侍从之列\N{\rEnglish}Bring her into my personal service.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:54.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}并记得为我祈祷\N{\rEnglish}And pray for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.32,0:11:56.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一如既往，大人\N{\rEnglish}As always, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.60,0:12:03.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:05.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:07.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德\N{\rEnglish}Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.00,0:12:11.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}东盎格利亚的埃德蒙国王来信，请求援兵\N{\rEnglish}King Edmund of East Anglia writes for an army.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.20,0:12:14.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们将不可避免地受到丹麦首领乌巴伯爵发起的进攻\N{\rEnglish}An attack by Danish Chieftain, Earl Ubba, is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.12,0:12:16.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是两天前的事\N{\rEnglish}This was two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.80,0:12:21.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}长途跋涉去他们选好的地方打，这种仗根本不值得考虑\N{\rEnglish}A long march to fight at a place of their choosing is not worth considering.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:24.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 说的算轻的了       - 我倾向于拒绝\N{\rEnglish}- To say the least. - I'm of a mind to decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.60,0:12:27.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 理应如此   - 乌巴，就是那个丹麦人，\N{\rEnglish}- And rightly. - Ubba, he is the Dane
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.80,0:12:30.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}埃德蒙国王以前一直供养着的那个？\N{\rEnglish}whom King Edmund has fed and watered in the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.52,0:12:32.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 正是   - 也许他是希望乌巴\N{\rEnglish}- He is. - Perhaps in the hope he would pass
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.96,0:12:35.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}借道东盎格利亚去入侵威塞克斯\N{\rEnglish}through East Anglia on his way to invading Wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.72,0:12:38.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}在我看来埃德蒙国王不值得支援\N{\rEnglish}It's my opinion that Edmund deserves nothing but silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.44,0:12:40.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}太无情了，小奥达\N{\rEnglish}Too harsh, Young Odda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:43.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}埃德蒙一心想用善意感化丹麦人，让他们从异教徒皈依基督\N{\rEnglish}It was Edmund's hope to convert the Danes from pagan to Christian
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.00,0:12:47.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}出发点是仁慈，这份心意理应得到称赞\N{\rEnglish}beginning with charity. For that, he deserves praise, surely.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:50.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 若真是这样的话，确实    - 埃德蒙是个虔诚的人\N{\rEnglish}- True, if that was his hope. - Edmund is a Godly man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.92,0:12:53.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们没理由把他的行为误解为懦弱\N{\rEnglish}We have no reason to mistake his actions for cowardice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.80,0:12:56.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不管他的用意如何，除非出现奇迹\N{\rEnglish}(ATHELRED) Regardless of intentions, barring a miracle,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.48,0:12:58.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}东盎格利亚终将落入丹麦人之手\N{\rEnglish}East Anglia will fall to Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.36,0:13:00.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们会为这奇迹降临而祈祷\N{\rEnglish}He shall have our prayers for such a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:03.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他会需要的      - 威塞克斯不会\N{\rEnglish}- He will need them. - (ATHELRED) He will not
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.16,0:13:04.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}派出一兵一卒，大家都同意？\N{\rEnglish}have one man of Wessex, we are agreed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.52,0:13:06.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是，大人 - 是\N{\rEnglish}- Yes, lord - Aye.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.36,0:13:11.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那我们必须承认，我们如今孤立无援\N{\rEnglish}Then we must therefore recognise that we now stand alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.60,0:13:14.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}英格兰最后一个王国\N{\rEnglish}The last kingdom of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.96,0:13:18.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}很快就会有威塞克斯的男人站在战场上，直面那支大军\N{\rEnglish}It will soon be men of Wessex staring across a field at the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.52,0:13:21.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们必须做好准备，我们要祈祷，要备战\N{\rEnglish}We must be ready. We must pray, we must prepare.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.64,0:13:26.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奥达，我需要你密切监视麦西亚、伦敦和东盎格利亚\N{\rEnglish}Odda, I require Mercia, Lundene and East Anglia be watched carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.28,0:13:27.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 掌握先机，才能制胜 - 遵命，大人\N{\rEnglish}- Forward knowledge is everything. - It is done, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.12,0:13:31.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}抄书员，我需要每座城镇的铁匠炉日夜不停地烧\N{\rEnglish}Scribe, I require the forges of every town burning, night and day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.88,0:13:34.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们需要那些炉火锻出的铁\N{\rEnglish}We need the iron those fires can proffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.16,0:13:36.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}遵命，大人\N{\rEnglish}(SCRIBE) Yes, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.56,0:13:38.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}最重要的，我需要人\N{\rEnglish}Most of all, I require men.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.68,0:13:43.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}强壮的、能打仗的人，他们要做好赴死的准备\N{\rEnglish}Strong, fighting men who are prepared to die
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:47.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}因为到最后,，能拯救我们的\N{\rEnglish}because that, in the end, is what it will take to save us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.12,0:13:52.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就是战士的鲜血\N{\rEnglish}The blood of men.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.40,0:13:58.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}拉文过去常说，"永远别去和乌巴作战"\N{\rEnglish}Ravn used to say, "Never fight Ubba."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.92,0:14:04.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}看来东盎格利亚刚犯了这个错\N{\rEnglish}Looks like East Anglia's just made that mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.92,0:14:09.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们应该远离这个地方\N{\rEnglish}(BRIDA) We should stay away for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.96,0:14:12.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去生我们自己的火吧\N{\rEnglish}Build our own fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.84,0:14:17.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴喜怒无常，他只听众神的旨意\N{\rEnglish}Ubba is unpredictable. He takes his orders from the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.84,0:14:20.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我知道他只听一个巫师的话\N{\rEnglish}I know he only listens to a sorcerer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:22.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而且他有点疯\N{\rEnglish}And he's half mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.64,0:14:24.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你打算怎么去见他?\N{\rEnglish}How will you approach him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.64,0:14:26.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}作为一个男人\N{\rEnglish}As a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.60,0:14:30.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这件事必须去做\N{\rEnglish}It has to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.04,0:14:33.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是的，必须去做\N{\rEnglish}Yes, it has to be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.28,0:14:35.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我们得保住你的命\N{\rEnglish}But we need to guard your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.72,0:14:39.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 怎么做? - 我不知道\N{\rEnglish}- How? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.20,0:14:48.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}今晚我们该做爱\N{\rEnglish}We should hump tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.56,0:14:53.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们应该做爱，这是天意\N{\rEnglish}We should. it's written.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.08,0:14:56.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天意让我们做爱?\N{\rEnglish}That we should hump?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.88,0:15:01.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们的命运就是今晚做爱\N{\rEnglish}Our destiny is to hump, tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.32,0:15:02.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.00,0:15:18.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 光想想就让我兴奋     - 今晚你也只能想想了\N{\rEnglish}- I'm enjoying the thought of it. - That's all you'll enjoy tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.32,0:15:19.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.16,0:15:27.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.40,0:15:30.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 停, 停, 停 - 什么? 怎么了?\N{\rEnglish}- Stop. Stop. Stop. - What? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.28,0:15:32.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我想到办法了\N{\rEnglish}I think I have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.08,0:15:36.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们抓一个人质\N{\rEnglish}We take a hostage,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.32,0:15:39.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}当挡箭牌，保你一命\N{\rEnglish}a shield, a guarantee for your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.76,0:15:41.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}抓谁?\N{\rEnglish}Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.44,0:15:43.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还不知道\N{\rEnglish}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.04,0:15:46.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}抓他离不开的人\N{\rEnglish}Someone he can't do without.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.68,0:15:49.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}斯托里，他的巫师\N{\rEnglish}Storri, his sorcerer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.20,0:15:55.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.92,0:16:04.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这女人是谁?\N{\rEnglish}(DANE 1) Who is this woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.76,0:16:07.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她怎么还没躺下（来伺候人）？\N{\rEnglish}Why is she not on her back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.48,0:16:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不关你的事，她是给斯托里的\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) Not that it's your concern, but she's for Storri.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.12,0:16:13.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴送来的撒克逊婊子\N{\rEnglish}A Saxon whore, from Ubba.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.20,0:16:15.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我见过你\N{\rEnglish}I've seen you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.36,0:16:18.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我曾效命于拉格纳伯爵，现在效命于乌巴\N{\rEnglish}I served Earl Ragnar and now I serve Ubba.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.52,0:16:20.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 闭嘴, 女人\N{\rEnglish}-(DANE 2) Quiet, woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.60,0:16:22.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}小子，你肯定还会再见到我的\N{\rEnglish}You'll see me again, I'm sure, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:24.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:27.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 听说斯托里在教堂? - 是修道院,\N{\rEnglish}- I'm told Storri is at the church? - Monastery,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.64,0:16:31.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他在那儿看押埃德蒙国王，杀他的神父们\N{\rEnglish}looking after King Edmund and killing his priests.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.16,0:16:34.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.24,0:16:46.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.80,0:16:55.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.36,0:17:02.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 有人吗？   - 快走，否则你死定了\N{\rEnglish}- (UHTRED) Hello? - Leave or it will be the death of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.64,0:17:08.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 这座教堂是乌巴命令归我的   - 斯托里大人，我给你带来一份礼物\N{\rEnglish}- This church is mine by order of Ubba. - Master Storri, I have a gift for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.04,0:17:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 哦？  - 是伯爵乌巴送的\N{\rEnglish}- Really? - She's from Earl Ubba.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.12,0:17:12.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个女人？\N{\rEnglish}A woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.20,0:17:15.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴为什么送个女人来？我不需要\N{\rEnglish}Why would Ubba send a woman? I have no need.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.64,0:17:18.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她是个女巫，乌巴想要她死，但又怕被她诅咒\N{\rEnglish}She's a sorceress. He wishes her dead, but is afraid of a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.44,0:17:24.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}胸也垂，口气也臭，但你会得到报酬的\N{\rEnglish}Saggy tits, stinking breath, but you will be rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.20,0:17:25.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}赏金是她脑袋等重的白银\N{\rEnglish}Her head's weight in silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.12,0:17:28.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}女巫？\N{\rEnglish}(STORRI) A Sorceress?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.88,0:17:32.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她长了张母狼的脸，会咬人吗？\N{\rEnglish}She has the face of a she-wolf. Does she bite?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.80,0:17:36.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 会，她会咬人 - 把她留给我\N{\rEnglish}- Yes, she bites. - Leave her with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.84,0:17:40.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会照乌巴的意思办，让她死得很慢\N{\rEnglish}I will do as Ubba asks and she will die slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.40,0:17:41.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.56,0:17:45.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}老头，你现在是我的人了\N{\rEnglish}You belong to me now, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.52,0:17:49.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}要是不听我的话，你就死得很慢\N{\rEnglish}And you will die slowly unless you do as I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.56,0:17:51.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}站起来\N{\rEnglish}On your feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.16,0:17:55.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们出去走走，给我闭上嘴\N{\rEnglish}We're going for a walk and you will keep your mouth shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.08,0:17:57.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:18:00.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这太蠢了\N{\rEnglish}This is so foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.92,0:18:03.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴会来找我的\N{\rEnglish}Ubba will come look for me
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.28,0:18:05.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他很快就到    - 我说了让你闭嘴\N{\rEnglish}- and he will be here soon. - I said be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.00,0:18:07.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那我就在这等他\N{\rEnglish}Then I'll wait for him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.68,0:18:09.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我在这等乌巴\N{\rEnglish}I'll wait for Ubba here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.84,0:18:14.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这就意味着只剩你我二人了\N{\rEnglish}That means it's just you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.72,0:18:26.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.44,0:18:28.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.60,0:18:32.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}斯托里在哪？ 他应该在这里的\N{\rEnglish}(UBBA) Where is Storri? He's supposed to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.00,0:18:36.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}埃德蒙\N{\rEnglish}Edmund.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.32,0:18:39.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}埃德蒙\N{\rEnglish}Edmund.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:41.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}埃德蒙\N{\rEnglish}Edmund.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.48,0:18:44.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}埃德蒙\N{\rEnglish}Edmund
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.24,0:18:45.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.76,0:18:47.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}能给我们来点麦酒吗？\N{\rEnglish}Can we have some ale?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:50.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}可怜的东盎格利亚国王埃德蒙\N{\rEnglish}Miserable King Edmund of East Anglia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.08,0:18:53.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你已经有一整晚考虑我的条件了\N{\rEnglish}You have had the night to consider my offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.68,0:18:55.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你怎么答复？\N{\rEnglish}How do you answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.48,0:18:56.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.96,0:19:00.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你是死是活？ - 但愿他死了\N{\rEnglish}- Are you dead or breathing still? - (GUTHRUM) With luck he's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.20,0:19:03.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们已经留了太多人活着了\N{\rEnglish}We allow far too many of them to live as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.16,0:19:05.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你做不了这个主    - 他还活着\N{\rEnglish}- You allow nothing. - He lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.72,0:19:07.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谁生谁死，由天主决定\N{\rEnglish}It's God who decides who lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.68,0:19:10.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我倒觉得，你的天主已经抛弃你了，大人\N{\rEnglish}I would say your God has left you hanging, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.28,0:19:13.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}若真如此，那也是他的旨意\N{\rEnglish}(EDMUND) If he has done so, it's because it is his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.52,0:19:18.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}把他放下来， 别让他倒在地上\N{\rEnglish}Take him down, and do not to let him fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.36,0:19:21.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 给他一杯麦酒，古思伦伯爵也来一杯    - 我不明白\N{\rEnglish}- And ale, and for the Earl Guthrum. - (GUTHRUM) I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.68,0:19:24.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们一直都是这么干的，留一半人活命\N{\rEnglish}We do this all the time. We allow half to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.28,0:19:26.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我说全杀了，只留年轻女人\N{\rEnglish}I say we kill them all. All but the young women.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.96,0:19:28.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那谁来耕田？\N{\rEnglish}(UBBA) And who should work the fields?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.08,0:19:31.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}老女人和孕妇\N{\rEnglish}(GUTHRUM) The old women, the pregnant women.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.72,0:19:33.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}把他放在那\N{\rEnglish}(UBBA) Put him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.72,0:19:36.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 给这位大人倒杯麦酒    - 乌巴伯爵?\N{\rEnglish}- And give the man some ale. - Earl Ubba?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.20,0:19:39.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}请允许我直说\N{\rEnglish}If I may speak freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.80,0:19:41.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我认识你\N{\rEnglish}I know you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.36,0:19:45.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我是乌特雷德·拉格纳松，我来是为了告诉你我父亲真正的死因\N{\rEnglish}I'm Uhtred Ragnarson. I am here with the truth of how my father died.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.44,0:19:48.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你是拉格纳的奴隶，是你杀了他\N{\rEnglish}Yes, you are Ragnar's slave and you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.00,0:19:52.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我不知道你听到什么，拉格纳伯爵是被丹麦人杀死的\N{\rEnglish}I don't know what you've heard, but Earl Ragnar was killed by Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.72,0:19:57.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就是他以前的船长基尔坦和他那独眼的儿子斯文\N{\rEnglish}His former ship's master Kjartan and his half-blind son Sven,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.24,0:20:01.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他们趁夜偷袭了熟睡中的众人 - 没见我们正在待客吗?\N{\rEnglish}-they led the attack on a sleeping party. - Can't see we're entertaining?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.32,0:20:04.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴大人，我告诉你，拉格纳是被丹麦人杀死的\N{\rEnglish}Lord Ubba, I'm telling you, Ragnar was killed by Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.36,0:20:07.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你给我闭嘴，等着 - 杀了他\N{\rEnglish}- You be quiet, boy. And you will wait. - Kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.80,0:20:09.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}别跟他废话\N{\rEnglish}(UBBA) Not another word.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.28,0:20:11.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}封住门，不许他离开\N{\rEnglish}Bar the doors, he does not leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.24,0:20:13.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}古思伦说得对，我们正在招待一位国王\N{\rEnglish}Guthrum is right. We are entertaining a king,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.76,0:20:15.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不要再打扰了\N{\rEnglish}so no more interruptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.80,0:20:18.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我只是想知道，那是谁?\N{\rEnglish}I just have to know, who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:19.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}嗯?\N{\rEnglish}Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.12,0:20:24.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他的眼睛正盯着我     - 也盯着我\N{\rEnglish}- His eyes are watching me. - And me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.00,0:20:26.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}什么谁?\N{\rEnglish}Who's what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.64,0:20:29.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 谁?     - 那边那个半裸的像\N{\rEnglish}- Who? - The half-naked image there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.24,0:20:32.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那是谁?\N{\rEnglish}Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.72,0:20:34.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.20,0:20:35.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那是圣塞巴斯蒂安\N{\rEnglish}That is Saint Sebastian.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.92,0:20:37.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他曾是罗马士兵，后来皈依（找到）了天主\N{\rEnglish}A former Roman soldier who found God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.08,0:20:39.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}在哪里找到的天主?\N{\rEnglish}(GUTHRUM) Found him where?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.04,0:20:42.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他在… 他在心中找到了天主，而不是\N{\rEnglish}He ...He found him in his heart, not
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.24,0:20:48.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你想听他的故事吗?    - 我有时间\N{\rEnglish}- Do you wish me to tell you his story? - I have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.20,0:20:57.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}皇帝得知塞巴斯蒂安皈依了天主\N{\rEnglish}(EDMUND) The emperor, discovering that Sebastian had found God,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.28,0:20:59.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}命令他放弃信仰，他拒绝了\N{\rEnglish}ordered him to renounce his faith, he refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.96,0:21:04.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}于是皇帝下令用箭将他射穿\N{\rEnglish}So then the emperor ordered that he be filled full of arrows
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.36,0:21:06.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他却活了下来\N{\rEnglish}and yet he lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.72,0:21:10.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他活下来了? - 是的，他活了\N{\rEnglish}- He lived? - Yes, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.72,0:21:12.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 这是真的吗? - 当然是真的\N{\rEnglish}- Is this true? - Of course, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.48,0:21:16.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主拯救了圣塞巴斯蒂安，愿天主因这份慈悲而受赞颂\N{\rEnglish}God saved St Sebastian and God should be praised for that mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.04,0:21:18.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他又活了多久?\N{\rEnglish}For how long did he live?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.80,0:21:21.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}唉, 可惜他…\N{\rEnglish}Well, sadly he--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.44,0:21:24.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}皇帝随后又下令将他活活打死\N{\rEnglish}He then ordered him to be clubbed to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.48,0:21:29.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 所以他还是死了? - 他去了天堂，所以他活着\N{\rEnglish}- So he died? - He went to heaven, so he lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.64,0:21:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我听说过这个天堂    - 什么是天堂?\N{\rEnglish}- I heard mention of this heaven. - What is this heaven?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.36,0:21:37.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天堂就是基督徒的英灵殿，只是没有战斗、宴饮和欢爱\N{\rEnglish}Heaven is Valhalla to Christians without fighting, feasting, humping.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.32,0:21:40.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天堂就是天堂\N{\rEnglish}Heaven is heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.36,0:21:42.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不是什么异教的东西\N{\rEnglish}It's not heathen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.68,0:21:45.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不过，回到你最初的问题\N{\rEnglish}But to answer your very first question,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.08,0:21:47.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我已经考虑过你的提议了\N{\rEnglish}I have considered your offer
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.88,0:21:51.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我同意，我会按你说的继续统治东盎格利亚\N{\rEnglish}and, yes, I will continue to rule East Anglia as you suggest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.68,0:21:53.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会忍受你的存在\N{\rEnglish}I will suffer your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.52,0:21:57.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会为你提供战马、粮食、钱币\N{\rEnglish}I will provide you with horses, food, coin,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.48,0:21:59.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还有人质\N{\rEnglish}and hostages.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.16,0:22:01.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你要求的，我都会照做\N{\rEnglish}I will do all that you demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.36,0:22:07.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但前提是，乌巴大人\N{\rEnglish}But only if you, Lord Ubba,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.00,0:22:10.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你和你所有的手下\N{\rEnglish}and all of your men
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.48,0:22:12.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}都必须归顺天主\N{\rEnglish}submit to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.00,0:22:14.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是我的条件\N{\rEnglish}That is my demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.72,0:22:17.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你们必须接受洗礼\N{\rEnglish}You must be baptised.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.96,0:22:25.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}站进一桶水里，让他们再往你身上浇水\N{\rEnglish}You must stand in a barrel of water and they pour more water over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.16,0:22:29.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他们要给我洗澡?    - 不是\N{\rEnglish}- They want to wash me? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.64,0:22:33.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是你的体味熏到他们了，乌巴     - 不，是要洗净你的罪孽\N{\rEnglish}- Your scent upsets them, Ubba. - No, to cleanse you of your sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.24,0:22:36.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}只有一位真神，我要求你臣服于他\N{\rEnglish}There is only one God, and I demand that you serve him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.56,0:22:38.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 现在就宰了他! - 我为什么要臣服于他?\N{\rEnglish}- Kill him now! - Why must I serve him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.88,0:22:41.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}因为天主伟大，全能，无上荣光\N{\rEnglish}Because God is great, all-powerful, magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.56,0:22:44.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让他别废话了, 拿出证明来!\N{\rEnglish}Have him stop his yapping and prove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.44,0:22:47.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}好, 说定了, 向我证明你的天主有多伟大, 证明给我看\N{\rEnglish}Ah. Agreed. Prove to me your God is great. Prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.04,0:22:51.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}证明, 证明, 证明——你看, 就在这里!\N{\rEnglish}Prove, prove, prove-- Look, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.16,0:22:53.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主庇佑了圣塞巴斯蒂安\N{\rEnglish}God spared Saint Sebastian.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.44,0:22:55.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 但那人还是死了 - 那是天主的旨意\N{\rEnglish}- But the man died. - It was God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.76,0:22:57.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主能护你不被我的箭射死吗?\N{\rEnglish}Would God protect you from my arrows?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.84,0:23:01.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 如果他真是全能的, 应该能? - 是的, 若是天主的旨意, 他会的\N{\rEnglish}- If he was all-powerful, he would? - Yes, if it was God's will, he would.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.00,0:23:03.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那就来试试看\N{\rEnglish}(UBBA) So let us try.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.00,0:23:09.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们朝你射箭, 你要是活下来\N{\rEnglish}We shall shoot arrows at you, and if you survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.16,0:23:10.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.08,0:23:14.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们全都去受洗\N{\rEnglish}we will all be washed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.24,0:23:17.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 包括古思伦 - 为什么不呢?\N{\rEnglish}- Including Guthrum here. - Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.72,0:23:25.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}好吧\N{\rEnglish}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.80,0:23:32.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我仍会继续做国王,\N{\rEnglish}I will continue to be king
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.00,0:23:36.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我们就不必去受那个洗礼了\N{\rEnglish}but we will dispense with the need for baptisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.40,0:23:38.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}洗礼之事\N{\rEnglish}The washing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.44,0:23:39.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我撤回请求\N{\rEnglish}I withdraw my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.08,0:23:43.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但你说你的天主是全能的\N{\rEnglish}But you claim your God is all-powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:23:45.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我要亲眼见到\N{\rEnglish}I want it proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.80,0:23:49.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}剥掉他的衣服，弓箭手准备\N{\rEnglish}Strip him. Archers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.08,0:23:57.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}等等\N{\rEnglish}(GUTHRUM) wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.80,0:24:05.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}老实告诉我\N{\rEnglish}Tell me truthfully,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.64,0:24:08.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你怕吗?\N{\rEnglish}are you afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.44,0:24:11.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}天主是伟大的\N{\rEnglish}God is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.36,0:24:15.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们走着瞧\N{\rEnglish}We will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.32,0:24:21.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}射\N{\rEnglish}Shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.52,0:24:25.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 射      - 慢着\N{\rEnglish}- Shoot. - Uh-uh-uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.36,0:24:30.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们是我的人，只有我才能命令他们射箭\N{\rEnglish}They are my men and only I tell them when to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.08,0:24:33.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}射\N{\rEnglish}Shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.32,0:24:37.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.00,0:24:41.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你是要挨棍子，还是这几箭已经够了?\N{\rEnglish}Do you wish to be clubbed or are the arrows sufficient?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.16,0:24:50.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你跑这么远来告诉我杀拉格纳的是丹麦人，不是你\N{\rEnglish}You come a long way, boy, to tell me that it was Danes and not you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.80,0:24:52.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rEnglish}that killed Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.68,0:24:54.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是基尔坦和斯文，大人\N{\rEnglish}It was Kjartan and Sven, lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.92,0:24:56.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还有其他人\N{\rEnglish}and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.64,0:25:00.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是实话，不然我来这儿干什么?\N{\rEnglish}It's the truth. Why else would I be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.20,0:25:02.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}来刺探，来撒谎\N{\rEnglish}To spy, to lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.32,0:25:04.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 不是，大人\N{\rEnglish}- No, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.40,0:25:06.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 也许是来杀我? - 不是，大人\N{\rEnglish}- Perhaps to kill me? - No, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.96,0:25:10.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你受洗了吗? - 奥丁才是我的神\N{\rEnglish}- Have you been washed? - Odin is my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.00,0:25:13.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但你受洗了?\N{\rEnglish}(GUTHRUM) But you have been washed?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.00,0:25:17.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是的，大人 - 感觉怎么样？\N{\rEnglish}- Yes, lord. - How did it feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.60,0:25:22.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 洗礼？ - 很冷，大人，水很冷\N{\rEnglish}- The washing? - Cold, lord. The water was cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.40,0:25:24.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没其他感觉？\N{\rEnglish}(GUTHRUM) Nothing else?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.00,0:25:27.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我曾是个孩子，大人，如今我是丹麦人了\N{\rEnglish}I was a child, lord. Now I'm a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.88,0:25:29.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}对，丹麦人\N{\rEnglish}Yeah, a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.32,0:25:37.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}好，现在我们来看看\N{\rEnglish}So, now let us see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.36,0:25:40.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}奥丁能不能护你躲过箭雨\N{\rEnglish}if Odin will protect you from the arrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.04,0:25:45.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我喜欢这个游戏，扒了他的衣服 - 别靠近我\N{\rEnglish}- I like this game. Strip him. - (UHTRED) Keep away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.76,0:25:48.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 别再靠近了 - 弓箭手\N{\rEnglish}- Not another step. - (UBBA) Archers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.68,0:25:50.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我有人质 - 什么？\N{\rEnglish}- I have a hostage. - (UBBA) What?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.40,0:25:51.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我抓住了斯托里 - 住手\N{\rEnglish}- I have Storri. - Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.12,0:25:55.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果我死，他也死，如果我死，你的巫师也死\N{\rEnglish}If I die, he dies. If I die, your sorcerer dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.20,0:25:57.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你就会失去他的指引了 - 他在撒谎，我闻得出来\N{\rEnglish}- and you're without his guidance. - He lies, I smell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.00,0:26:01.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我有证据，这是他的符文\N{\rEnglish}I have proof. His runes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.72,0:26:07.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我会把斯托里还给你 - 把他脑袋砍下来\N{\rEnglish}- Storri will be returned to you. - Take his head from his shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.72,0:26:11.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 古思伦，闭嘴 - 让他们打开门\N{\rEnglish}- Guthrum, be quiet. - Have them open the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.96,0:26:14.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我离开这里之后，就会放了斯托里\N{\rEnglish}I will release Storri when I am clear of this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.84,0:26:18.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你哪儿都别想去 - 那他就死，你的巫师就死\N{\rEnglish}- (UBBA) You go nowhere. - Then he dies. Your sorcerer dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.64,0:26:22.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让他们把门打开\N{\rEnglish}Have them open the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.72,0:26:31.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.40,0:26:37.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}总有一天我会杀了你\N{\rEnglish}One day I will kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.84,0:26:40.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}斯托里会告诉你不是这样的\N{\rEnglish}Storri will tell you otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.24,0:26:45.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}关于拉格纳的事，我说的是实话\N{\rEnglish}And I am telling you the truth about Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.96,0:26:58.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这就是留太多人活命的下场\N{\rEnglish}This is what happens when we allow too many to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.04,0:27:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.44,0:27:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}好极了，柴火\N{\rEnglish}Excellent. Firewood.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.76,0:27:10.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你还活着\N{\rEnglish}You're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.84,0:27:12.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}很好\N{\rEnglish}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.56,0:27:14.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他相信你吗？\N{\rEnglish}Did he hear you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.28,0:27:16.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没有，一个字都不信\N{\rEnglish}He did not. Not a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.00,0:27:19.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他说什么了? - 说要杀我\N{\rEnglish}- What did he say? - That he'll kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.84,0:27:21.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就这些?\N{\rEnglish}Nothing else?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.76,0:27:23.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}斯托里在哪?\N{\rEnglish}Where's Storri?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.92,0:27:25.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他说什么了?\N{\rEnglish}(BRIDA) what did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.96,0:27:30.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他没穿衣服 - 这是必要的\N{\rEnglish}- He's naked. - It was necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.20,0:27:33.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他屁股上插了根树枝\N{\rEnglish}He has a branch up his arse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.32,0:27:35.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}所以他才没穿衣服\N{\rEnglish}Which is why he's naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.44,0:27:37.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}(BRIDA) Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.12,0:27:45.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.00,0:27:50.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德，他肯定说了什么\N{\rEnglish}Uhtred, he must have said something.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.24,0:27:55.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他信了那个谎，他以为是我杀了拉格纳\N{\rEnglish}He believes the lie. He believes that I killed Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.44,0:28:02.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.08,0:28:07.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没有其他办法了\N{\rEnglish}There's nothing more to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.44,0:28:10.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.76,0:28:14.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们得赶紧离这儿远一点\N{\rEnglish}We should put distance between us and this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.48,0:28:15.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去哪?\N{\rEnglish}And go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.16,0:28:18.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}哪儿都行，只要不是这里\N{\rEnglish}Anywhere that's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.64,0:28:23.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我说去找小拉格纳 - 他在爱尔兰\N{\rEnglish}- I say we go to young Ragnar. - He's in Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.64,0:28:27.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 那就去爱尔兰 - 怎么去? 坐什么? 坐什么船?\N{\rEnglish}- Then we go to Ireland. - How? In what? We sail in what?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.16,0:28:29.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 跟谁去? 丹麦人? - 那就等他回来\N{\rEnglish}- And with whom? Danes? - Then we wait for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.76,0:28:32.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}要是他回不来了，那该怎么办?\N{\rEnglish}What if he doesn't return, what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.64,0:28:37.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}认了吧，我们输了\N{\rEnglish}Accept it, we lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.60,0:28:43.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我们还活着，肯定有原因 - 布丽达，我们已经不是丹麦人了\N{\rEnglish}- We're alive and breathing for a reason. - Brida, we are no longer Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.96,0:29:26.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你的兵器怎么收钱?\N{\rEnglish}How much for your work?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.76,0:29:29.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rEnglish}00:29:27,730 --> 00:29:29,580\N{\rChinese}一柄长剑\N{\rEnglish}For a long sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.32,0:29:31.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}说说你要什么，我再报价\N{\rEnglish}Tell me what you need and I'll tell you a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.28,0:29:35.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一把能用一辈子的战士之剑\N{\rEnglish}A warrior sword to last a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.40,0:29:37.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你是哪边的?\N{\rEnglish}What are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.64,0:29:40.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}撒克逊人还是丹麦人?\N{\rEnglish}Saxon or Dane?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.32,0:29:42.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}诺森布里亚人\N{\rEnglish}Northumbria.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.44,0:29:47.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}打好这把剑得花些时日\N{\rEnglish}It'll take some time to make her right,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.56,0:29:51.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}所以价钱不会低\N{\rEnglish}which means she'll be expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.00,0:29:54.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果做的好，我会用银子付\N{\rEnglish}She's right, I'll pay in silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.20,0:29:55.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}多少?\N{\rEnglish}How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.04,0:29:57.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}十枚，先付一半\N{\rEnglish}Ten pieces. Half now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.68,0:29:59.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}六枚，不能再多了\N{\rEnglish}(LAUGHS) Six. No more.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.44,0:30:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}八枚，我给你打把最好的\N{\rEnglish}Eight, and I'll make her my finest.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.52,0:30:04.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}八枚，如果不是你最好的手艺，你就第一个尝尝她的厉害\N{\rEnglish}Eight, if she is not your finest, you'll be her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.88,0:30:15.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我想把这块石头嵌进剑柄里\N{\rEnglish}I want this stone set into the handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.28,0:30:20.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没问题\N{\rEnglish}That can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.12,0:30:23.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}别卖掉，也别弄丢了\N{\rEnglish}Don't sell it nor lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.20,0:30:43.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}要来点麦酒吗，大人?\N{\rEnglish}(SERVANT) Ale, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.24,0:30:45.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 站远一点，姑娘    - 好，就一点点\N{\rEnglish}- You stand too close, girl. - (ALFRED) Yes, just a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.12,0:30:49.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 去去粥的味道     - 站远一点\N{\rEnglish}- To take away the taste of the gruel. - You stand too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.88,0:30:52.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是浓汤，不是粥\N{\rEnglish}It is broth, not gruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.40,0:30:53.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是吗?\N{\rEnglish}- Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.12,0:30:58.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我觉得是，你该感谢天主的恩典\N{\rEnglish}Well, I think it is. You should be thanking God of its goodness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.20,0:31:01.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让那些难受的腹痛都消散了\N{\rEnglish}and the banishment of those awful cramps.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.16,0:31:03.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我很乐意和你吃一样的食物\N{\rEnglish}I am happy to eat as you eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.16,0:31:06.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你真是心善, 亲爱的   贝奥卡神父, 来跟我们一起用早餐吧\N{\rEnglish}You are saintly, my dear. Father Beocca, join us for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.00,0:31:10.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我允许你来  - 可惜, 大人, 我已经吃过了\N{\rEnglish}- I dare you. - Alas, my lord, I've already eaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.24,0:31:11.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你运气真好\N{\rEnglish}(ALFRED) You're fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.00,0:31:14.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 有坏消息 你的侄子埃塞尔沃尔德\N{\rEnglish}Bad news, lord. Your nephew, Aethelwold.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.08,0:31:17.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 坏消息总是和他有关   - 他喝醉了\N{\rEnglish}- (AELSWITH) Isn't it always? - He's drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.20,0:31:18.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他睡在宫殿的花园里\N{\rEnglish}He's sleeping in the palace garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.12,0:31:22.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}要把他带去见国王吗? 这已经是本周第二次了\N{\rEnglish}Should I take him to the king? It's the second time this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.52,0:31:25.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}愿天主让他痛苦地死去\N{\rEnglish}May God strike him down, painfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.00,0:31:31.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.00,0:31:33.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.68,0:31:35.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 什么? 什么? - 起来, 小子\N{\rEnglish}- What? What? - (LEOFRIC) On your feet, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.88,0:31:37.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}等等, 等等, 等等\N{\rEnglish}Wait, wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.36,0:31:40.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}快来, 国王要见你\N{\rEnglish}(BEOCCA) Come on, the king wants to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.60,0:31:42.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}喝醉了!\N{\rEnglish}Drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.80,0:31:44.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}什么, 又来了?\N{\rEnglish}What, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.68,0:31:46.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你觉得这像话吗?\N{\rEnglish}Do you think this is fit?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.40,0:31:48.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}都出去, 留我们单独说话\N{\rEnglish}Out, all of you, leave us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.96,0:31:54.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你觉得这像话吗? - 我受了虐待\N{\rEnglish}- Do you think this is fit? - I have been mistreated.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.68,0:31:58.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你亲眼看到了 我要求——\N{\rEnglish}You saw this for yourself. I demand that this--
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.36,0:32:00.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 这头混蛋受到惩罚 - 埃塞尔沃尔德,\N{\rEnglish}- This bear is punished. - (KING AETHELRED) Aethelwold,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.88,0:32:03.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你年纪不小了, 还是叫人失望\N{\rEnglish}your years do not hide the fact you are a disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.12,0:32:06.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 为什么? - 如果你还要问这个, 你父亲\N{\rEnglish}- Why? - That need to ask tells your father
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.84,0:32:09.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 就什么都明白了 - 明白了什么?\N{\rEnglish}- all he needs to know. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.08,0:32:13.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}明白了你不适合继承王位\N{\rEnglish}That you are an unsuitable heir. That is what.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.36,0:32:19.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 那我会改变的 - 你该改\N{\rEnglish}- Then I will change. - You should.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.56,0:32:21.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我会的 - 听着, 我只要求一件事\N{\rEnglish}- I will. - Look, all I ask
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.32,0:32:24.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你得快点成长为一个真正的男人\N{\rEnglish}is that you become a man, and quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.80,0:32:26.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就从今天开始\N{\rEnglish}Today.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.08,0:32:30.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}从今天开始, 我保证\N{\rEnglish}Today, I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.92,0:32:38.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我可以告退了吗?\N{\rEnglish}Am I excused?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.64,0:32:46.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人\N{\rEnglish}My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.28,0:32:53.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我怀疑他根本不是我的儿子\N{\rEnglish}I'm not convinced he is my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.96,0:32:57.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他母亲要不是已经死了, 我早就以通奸罪砍了她的头\N{\rEnglish}If his mother was not already dead, I'd have her beheaded for adultery.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.08,0:33:00.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.48,0:33:06.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果我在即将到来的战斗中阵亡,\N{\rEnglish}If I'm to fall in the battles that will come,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.12,0:33:09.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不能继承王位\N{\rEnglish}he cannot be king.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.60,0:33:13.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你倾向的是阿尔弗雷德吗 - 是的\N{\rEnglish}- You favour Alfred? - I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.56,0:33:17.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}即便他身体常常羸弱?\N{\rEnglish}Even though he is often weak in body?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.44,0:33:22.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}病痛没有把他困在床上, 这正是我弟弟的坚韧所在\N{\rEnglish}His illness does not tie him to bed, shows the strength of my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.44,0:33:26.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德是我的继承人, 他自己也清楚\N{\rEnglish}Alfred is my heir. He knows it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.24,0:33:31.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}时机一到, 奥达, 我的朋友,\N{\rEnglish}And when the time comes, Odda my friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.64,0:33:35.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你必须引导贤人会议做出这个选择\N{\rEnglish}you must steer the witan to make this choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.32,0:33:37.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人\N{\rEnglish}My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.36,0:33:45.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}搞完了\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.84,0:33:47.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}眼下应该安全了\N{\rEnglish}Should be safe for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.60,0:33:50.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}据说丹麦人很少来这里\N{\rEnglish}They say Danes rarely come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.88,0:33:54.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}斯托里跟你说了什么, 让你把他的嘴给堵上, 还有......\N{\rEnglish}What did Storri say to you to make you bind his mouth and, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.92,0:33:56.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他下了一个诅咒\N{\rEnglish}He threw a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.40,0:33:58.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}说什么?\N{\rEnglish}Saying what?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.40,0:33:59.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不重要\N{\rEnglish}It's not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.04,0:34:02.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我用树枝回应了\N{\rEnglish}I responded with the branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.00,0:34:08.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你在干什么?\N{\rEnglish}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.48,0:34:10.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你知道我在干什么\N{\rEnglish}You know what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.40,0:34:12.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我要用一个吻解除最后一道诅咒\N{\rEnglish}I'm removing the last curse with a kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.84,0:34:14.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我不想\N{\rEnglish}I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.00,0:34:23.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你若想去投奔丹麦人, 那就去找个新主人\N{\rEnglish}If you want to go to the Danes, then go find a new lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.72,0:34:28.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们想杀的是我\N{\rEnglish}It's me they wish to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.08,0:34:31.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你说话像个孩子 - 我是在给你选择\N{\rEnglish}- You sound like a child. - I'm offering a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.84,0:34:34.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你是在用屁股说话  - 我正坐在我的屁股上\N{\rEnglish}- Talking through your arse. - I'm sitting on my arse.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.80,0:34:38.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那你屁股比你聪明, 它能一心二用\N{\rEnglish}Your arse is cleverer than you, it can do two things at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.16,0:34:39.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}谢谢\N{\rEnglish}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.40,0:34:42.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你这女人, 嘴够毒的\N{\rEnglish}Your tongue is sharp, woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.80,0:34:44.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.28,0:34:47.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 再给我看一遍 - 不\N{\rEnglish}- Show me again. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.48,0:34:51.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你说得对\N{\rEnglish}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.48,0:34:54.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们不能去找小拉格纳\N{\rEnglish}We can't go to young Ragnar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.48,0:35:00.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我们应该等他来找我们\N{\rEnglish}But we should wait for him to find us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.32,0:35:03.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他会来的, 他想知道真相\N{\rEnglish}Which he will. He will want to know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.64,0:35:09.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}在那之前, 我们得活下去\N{\rEnglish}In the time between, we stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.40,0:35:12.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}打发时间\N{\rEnglish}We pass the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.16,0:35:14.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}怎么打发?\N{\rEnglish}Doing what?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.80,0:35:20.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.36,0:35:23.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.36,0:35:26.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.84,0:35:28.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.72,0:35:31.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.04,0:35:38.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.20,0:35:42.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.68,0:35:44.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.60,0:35:46.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.00,0:35:50.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.92,0:36:46.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我给她添了几分姿色\N{\rEnglish}I've given her some beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.72,0:36:50.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但她不过是个工具, 仅此而已\N{\rEnglish}But she is a tool, no more, no less.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.36,0:37:02.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她正是我期望的样子\N{\rEnglish}She is exactly as I'd hoped.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.80,0:37:05.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我们说好十个? - 我们说的是八个\N{\rEnglish}- We said ten? - We said eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.76,0:37:07.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}她值十个\N{\rEnglish}She's worth ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.12,0:37:11.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 谢了 - 谢了\N{\rEnglish}- Thank you. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.84,0:37:14.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 有人在打听你的下落\N{\rEnglish}Lord, men have been asking of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.20,0:37:16.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还有你的女人\N{\rEnglish}And your woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.00,0:37:19.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 丹麦人还是撒克逊人? - 随你选\N{\rEnglish}- Danes or Saxon? - Take your pick.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.80,0:37:21.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}五个或者更多\N{\rEnglish}Five or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.80,0:37:25.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让她颤鸣吧\N{\rEnglish}Make her sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.28,0:37:32.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们得走了, 有人在找我们\N{\rEnglish}We should leave. There are men looking for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.84,0:37:34.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是乌巴的人? - 不知道\N{\rEnglish}(BRIDA) From Ubba? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.48,0:37:36.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}撒克逊人和丹麦人都在找我们\N{\rEnglish}Saxons and Danes are looking for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.72,0:37:39.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们这一路好像到处都在树敌\N{\rEnglish}We seem to be collecting enemies as we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.32,0:37:49.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去找马, 快走快走!\N{\rEnglish}Get to the horses. Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.08,0:37:53.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.36,0:38:04.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让开  让开\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) Out of the way, out the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.52,0:38:12.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.24,0:38:45.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.16,0:39:12.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}布丽达, 马就在那边\N{\rEnglish}Bride. The horses are just there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.60,0:39:15.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}等等, 还有一个, 我们得走了, 跟我来\N{\rEnglish}Wait, there is another. We have to go. Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.32,0:39:22.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}快走, 快走, 让开!\N{\rEnglish}Move, move, move, out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.92,0:39:31.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 布丽达, 去开门 - 等等\N{\rEnglish}- Brida, the door. - Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.48,0:39:36.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}等着, 等着\N{\rEnglish}Wait. Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.76,0:39:39.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}现在!\N{\rEnglish}Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.28,0:39:45.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.32,0:39:47.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.04,0:39:52.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你说得对, 我们该走了\N{\rEnglish}You're right. We should leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.48,0:39:54.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不管是谁派他们来的,\N{\rEnglish}Whoever sent them,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.96,0:39:58.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴还是你叔父, 都不会罢手, 还会有更多人来\N{\rEnglish}Ubba or your uncle, they won't rest. There'll be others.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.92,0:40:05.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我没有援兵就回不了家\N{\rEnglish}I can't go home without help.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.08,0:40:09.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德, 你应该放弃贝班堡\N{\rEnglish}Uhtred, you should forget Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.04,0:40:13.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不\N{\rEnglish}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.52,0:40:15.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不, 我不会就此消失\N{\rEnglish}No, I won't vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.12,0:40:21.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}什么都不会变, 基尔坦和我叔父要为拉格纳的死付出代价,\N{\rEnglish}Nothing changes. Kjartan and my uncle will pay for Ragnar's death
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.32,0:40:24.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 那片土地也必须回到我手中 - 但怎么做?\N{\rEnglish}- and I will have those lands. - But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.72,0:40:26.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}靠谁的帮助?\N{\rEnglish}With whose help?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.80,0:40:29.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你自己也说了, 我们只有乌巴—— - 英格兰人\N{\rEnglish}- You said yourself, we only have Ubba-- - The English.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.32,0:40:33.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果我们在丹麦人眼里已经是死人, 那就别无选择\N{\rEnglish}If we're dead to the Danes, we have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.56,0:40:34.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}英格兰根本不存在\N{\rEnglish}There is no England.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.04,0:40:38.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 丹麦人占了英格兰 - 不, 南边还有一个地方\N{\rEnglish}- The Danes have England. - No, there is one place, south of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.16,0:40:42.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 那就是威塞克斯 - 他们看见你就会杀了你\N{\rEnglish}- it's Wessex. - They'll take one look and kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.40,0:40:44.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而乌巴会把我当英格兰人杀掉\N{\rEnglish}Whereas Ubba will kill me as an Englishman.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.80,0:40:48.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}跟着埃塞尔雷德国王, 我们就有一线生机\N{\rEnglish}With King Aethelred we have a chance, of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.20,0:40:50.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你怎么说?\N{\rEnglish}What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.64,0:40:53.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}跟我来?\N{\rEnglish}Come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.44,0:41:25.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们为什么盯着我们看?\N{\rEnglish}Why do they stare?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.84,0:41:28.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他们觉得你好看 - 哼\N{\rEnglish}- They think you're pretty. - Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.04,0:41:32.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}或者他们从没这么近见过丹麦人\N{\rEnglish}Or they have never seen a Dane so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.64,0:41:34.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但他们会见到的\N{\rEnglish}But they will.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.76,0:41:50.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.48,0:41:59.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.12,0:42:06.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.80,0:42:19.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我们有事要见埃塞尔雷德国王 - 滚回家去!\N{\rEnglish}- We have business with King Aethelred. - (MAN 1) Go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.04,0:42:21.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}当心\N{\rEnglish}(MAN 2) Careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.52,0:42:23.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我说了, 我们有事要见国王\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) I say we have business with the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.96,0:42:26.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你听不懂英语吗?\N{\rEnglish}Do you not understand English?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.80,0:42:30.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你说的那叫英语, 浑球? 你说话跟丹麦人一个腔调\N{\rEnglish}Is that what you're speaking, arseling? You sound like a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.32,0:42:33.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你一个种地的, 打扮得像个战士干什么?\N{\rEnglish}Why do you dress as a warrior when you're a farmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.04,0:42:38.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我种地?\N{\rEnglish}Farmer, am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.40,0:42:40.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}嗯，我敢说，我这农夫随时都能赢过你。\N{\rEnglish}I'd wager this farmer against you at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.04,0:42:43.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们是来和平觐见国王的\N{\rEnglish}We are here to see the king peaceably.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.16,0:42:45.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 乌特雷德, 你在干什么? - 怎么了?\N{\rEnglish}- Uhtred, what are you doing? - What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.60,0:42:47.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 见血就停还是打到死? - 乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}- First blood or to the death? - Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.68,0:42:51.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我要劈开你的脑袋, 小子, 所以一个接一个来\N{\rEnglish}I'll be splitting your skull, boy, so one follows the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.96,0:42:54.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.80,0:42:57.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 乌特雷德?\N{\rEnglish}- Uhtred?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.88,0:43:02.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝奥卡神父\N{\rEnglish}Father Beocca.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.56,0:43:03.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.04,0:43:06.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我的天     - 神父, 认识这个浑球?\N{\rEnglish}- My goodness. - Know this arseling, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.52,0:43:09.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}认识, 是的, 认识 乌特雷德, 你——\N{\rEnglish}(BEOCCA) I do. Yes, I do. Uhtred, you're--
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.60,0:43:12.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你都长这么大了\N{\rEnglish}You're fully grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.52,0:43:14.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而你却老了\N{\rEnglish}And you're old.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.00,0:43:16.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.48,0:43:18.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是啊\N{\rEnglish}I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.52,0:43:20.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你是个男人了\N{\rEnglish}You're a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.32,0:43:22.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他说有要事求见国王\N{\rEnglish}(LEOFRIC) He claims business with the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.44,0:43:23.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是的, 是真的\N{\rEnglish}Yes. Yes, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.00,0:43:25.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不是求见国王, 是找阿尔弗雷德\N{\rEnglish}But not with the king, with Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.08,0:43:28.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你为他担保? - 我为他担保, 是的\N{\rEnglish}- You vouch for him? - (BEOCCA) I vouch for him, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.72,0:43:31.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这定是天主派你来的\N{\rEnglish}God has sent you surely.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.84,0:43:33.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你已经是个男人了\N{\rEnglish}You're a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.04,0:43:37.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}神父, 这是布丽达\N{\rEnglish}Father, this is Brida,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.12,0:43:40.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我最好的朋友\N{\rEnglish}my greatest friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.44,0:43:41.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个女人\N{\rEnglish}A woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.12,0:43:44.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是的 - 没错\N{\rEnglish}- (UHTRED) Yes. - I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.36,0:43:52.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我有胸 - 我看见了\N{\rEnglish}- I have tits. - I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.44,0:43:55.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}让人喂好他们的马, 饮足水\N{\rEnglish}Have their horses fed and watered.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.80,0:43:57.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我去通报阿尔弗雷德你们到了\N{\rEnglish}And I will inform Alfred you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.88,0:44:01.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 神父, 要收他们的武器 - 为什么不去通报国王?\N{\rEnglish}- We need their weapons, Father. - Why not inform the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.44,0:44:03.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}国王正忙着\N{\rEnglish}The king is busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.32,0:44:04.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但你会喜欢阿尔弗雷德的\N{\rEnglish}But you will like Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.80,0:44:06.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他是个了不起的人\N{\rEnglish}He is an impressive man.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.16,0:44:09.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}跟我来\N{\rEnglish}Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.36,0:44:15.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.72,0:44:18.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你喜欢吗?\N{\rEnglish}Do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.56,0:44:21.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}喜欢\N{\rEnglish}I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.52,0:44:24.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}真美\N{\rEnglish}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.28,0:44:29.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你可以在这里歇息，多安静啊 - 宁静\N{\rEnglish}- You could rest here. it's so quiet. - (ALFRED) Peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.80,0:44:35.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}罗马人修建这座庭院，就是为了这个，求一份宁静\N{\rEnglish}The Romans, they built this courtyard for just that purpose. Tranquillity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.36,0:44:38.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你是阿尔弗雷德？ - 正是\N{\rEnglish}- You're Alfred? - I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.64,0:44:41.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 大人 - 你就是乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}- My lord. - (ALFRED) You are Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.76,0:44:45.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我听说你是个了不起的勇士\N{\rEnglish}I hear word you are a considerable warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.20,0:44:48.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}还没真正经历过考验，大人，还没有\N{\rEnglish}(LAUGHS) Not been tested, lord. Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.40,0:44:50.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我只是运气好\N{\rEnglish}And I've been lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.08,0:44:53.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}运气好，那也是好事\N{\rEnglish}Well, luck is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.32,0:44:55.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我的勇士们也是这么说的\N{\rEnglish}Or so my own warriors say.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.24,0:45:00.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}只是这运气背后的神学道理，我还没想通\N{\rEnglish}Now, I haven't quite worked out the theology of luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.64,0:45:03.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}若一切皆由天主主宰，运气又从何而来？\N{\rEnglish}Can there be luck if God disposes?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.64,0:45:08.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果你的天主与你同在，你自然是个幸运的人\N{\rEnglish}If your God is with you, you're a lucky man.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.88,0:45:12.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是，你说得对\N{\rEnglish}Yes. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.04,0:45:15.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}说得简单，但你说对了，跟我来\N{\rEnglish}Simply put, but you are right. With me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.88,0:45:18.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们进去说几句\N{\rEnglish}We shall talk inside briefly.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.72,0:45:34.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我有许多时间是在这里度过的\N{\rEnglish}I spend much of my time in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.28,0:45:37.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌特雷德，你识字吗？\N{\rEnglish}Do you read, Uhtred?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.44,0:45:39.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}小时候贝奥卡神父教过我\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) Schooled as a child by Father Beocca.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.84,0:45:41.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我不是个好学生\N{\rEnglish}I was not a good student.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.52,0:45:44.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 文字之外，有很多东西要学 - 这我毫不怀疑\N{\rEnglish}- There's much to know outside letters. - (ALFRED) I'm certain there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.28,0:45:49.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但不要小看文字的力量\N{\rEnglish}But do not underestimate the power of the written word.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.32,0:45:52.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个人死后，若无文字记载，他很快就会被人遗忘\N{\rEnglish}When a man dies, if nothing is written, he is soon forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.84,0:45:55.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就拿拉格纳伯爵来说，还有谁记得他？\N{\rEnglish}For instance, who is remembering Earl Ragnar?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.32,0:45:57.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你知道拉格纳？\N{\rEnglish}You know of Ragnar?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.92,0:46:01.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝奥卡神父跟我提起你很多次了, 乌特雷德\N{\rEnglish}Father Beocca has talked much about you, Uhtred.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.68,0:46:03.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他以为你被俘了\N{\rEnglish}He believed you a prisoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.04,0:46:06.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}沦为拉格纳伯爵的奴隶, 是这样吗?\N{\rEnglish}Slave to Earl Ragnar. Is that the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.28,0:46:08.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}拉格纳待我如父\N{\rEnglish}Ragnar was a father to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.36,0:46:12.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我深爱着他\N{\rEnglish}I loved him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.36,0:46:15.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但在约克, 人们都说是你杀了他\N{\rEnglish}Yet in Eofervvic, they're saying that you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.56,0:46:17.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们在撒谎\N{\rEnglish}They lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.12,0:46:23.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}基尔坦, 基尔坦, 这个名字是这样念的吗?\N{\rEnglish}Kjartan. Kjartan. Is that how you pronounce it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.52,0:46:25.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 基尔坦 - 基尔坦\N{\rEnglish}- Kjartan_ - Kjartan,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.60,0:46:28.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是从拉格纳的死中得益最大的人\N{\rEnglish}has benefited most from Ragnar's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.48,0:46:31.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他取而代之, 如今已是基尔坦伯爵了\N{\rEnglish}He has taken his place and is Earl Kjartan now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.48,0:46:34.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 一方大领主, 手握船队 - 这些都有记录?\N{\rEnglish}- A great lord, with ships. - That's written down?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.52,0:46:37.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}凡是我探到的关于敌人的消息, 都会记录在案\N{\rEnglish}Whatever I discover about enemies is written down.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.00,0:46:41.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}基尔坦杀你对他有利, 不是吗?\N{\rEnglish}It's in Kjartan's interest to kill you, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.76,0:46:45.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不想让拉格纳的儿子听到另一个版本\N{\rEnglish}He would not want Ragnar's son to hear a different tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.80,0:46:47.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他不想让他听到真相, 没错\N{\rEnglish}He would not wish him to hear the truth, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.88,0:46:50.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}没错, 还有头领乌巴,\N{\rEnglish}(ALFRED) No, and the Chieftain Ubba,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.00,0:46:53.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}尽管他本人已北上远行\N{\rEnglish}although he himself has now travelled north,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.44,0:46:56.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他派人去了麦西亚, 打听你的下落\N{\rEnglish}he has sent men to Mercia asking of your whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.12,0:46:59.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但不是关心你是否安好, 我猜?\N{\rEnglish}But not your welfare, I surmise?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.40,0:47:02.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这些消息你都是从哪儿得来的?\N{\rEnglish}How do you come by all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.20,0:47:05.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}各个王国里我都有耳目\N{\rEnglish}I have eyes and ears in each of the kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.56,0:47:11.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}有朝一日\N{\rEnglish}One day,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.44,0:47:15.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我希望所有的王国能合而为一\N{\rEnglish}it is my hope that all kingdoms will become one,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.08,0:47:19.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}在同一位天主的庇护下团结一心\N{\rEnglish}united under one God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.48,0:47:20.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一位国王?\N{\rEnglish}One king?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.52,0:47:24.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果所有人都能达成共识, 是的\N{\rEnglish}If all men can agree, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.52,0:47:30.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}英格兰如今只剩威塞克斯\N{\rEnglish}All that remains of England is Wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.68,0:47:33.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个英格兰的诞生,\N{\rEnglish}The birth of an England,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.80,0:47:38.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}一个叫做英格兰的统一王国的构想\N{\rEnglish}the idea of a single kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.92,0:47:41.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.76,0:47:43.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}必须从这里开始\N{\rEnglish}has to begin here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.04,0:47:46.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}别无他处\N{\rEnglish}There is nowhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.64,0:47:49.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但威塞克斯还能撑多久?\N{\rEnglish}But for how long will Wessex remain?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.72,0:47:54.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}威塞克斯的命运, 要由英格兰人来决定, 所有英格兰人\N{\rEnglish}The fate of Wessex will be determined by Englishmen, all Englishmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.44,0:47:59.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}只有团结起来守住威塞克斯, 才能有英格兰\N{\rEnglish}Only by joining together and saving Wessex can we have England.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.04,0:48:05.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}只有守住威塞克斯, 才能有诺森布里亚\N{\rEnglish}Only by saving Wessex can we have a Northumbria.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.20,0:48:07.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}才能有贝班堡\N{\rEnglish}A Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.72,0:48:09.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果威塞克斯守不住呢?\N{\rEnglish}And if Wessex can't be saved?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.04,0:48:12.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那我们就什么都没了\N{\rEnglish}Then we are all no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.48,0:48:15.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.64,0:48:17.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}祷告者们\N{\rEnglish}Prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.44,0:48:24.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.12,0:48:27.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我有点不舒服\N{\rEnglish}And a little discomfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.68,0:48:34.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我猜测\N{\rEnglish}I will summarise.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.08,0:48:37.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人正在集结一支大军\N{\rEnglish}The Danes are gathering a great army.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.12,0:48:40.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他们已经集结了一支军队 - 在哪里集结?\N{\rEnglish}- They have gathered an army. - Gather where?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.64,0:48:43.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们从伦敦沿河上行, 到了雷丁厄姆\N{\rEnglish}They moved upriver from Lundene to Readingum.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.24,0:48:45.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}此刻正在安营扎寨\N{\rEnglish}They are settling as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.24,0:48:47.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你说乌巴在北边, 那谁来领军?\N{\rEnglish}You say Ubba is north, so who leads?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.32,0:48:50.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 古思伦伯爵统领他们 - 我认识古思伦\N{\rEnglish}- The Earl Guthrum leads them. - I know Guthrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.84,0:48:55.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们得把每一分优势都用上\N{\rEnglish}We will need every advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.76,0:48:58.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝奥卡神父认为你\N{\rEnglish}And Father Beocca considers you,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.32,0:49:00.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝班堡的乌特雷德, 是个有用之人\N{\rEnglish}Uhtred of Bebbanburg, to be an advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.00,0:49:04.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而我认为你来这里不过是为了躲避\N{\rEnglish}Whereas I believe you are here solely to hide,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.84,0:49:07.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为了保全自己\N{\rEnglish}to save yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.00,0:49:11.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我看着你\N{\rEnglish}I look at you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.72,0:49:13.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}看到的是个丹麦人\N{\rEnglish}and I see a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.32,0:49:19.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我看到的是无处为家的乌特雷德, 只顾自己, 不管任何人\N{\rEnglish}I see Uhtred of Nowhere, who cares for no one but himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.72,0:49:25.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我得去祈祷了, 你来吗?\N{\rEnglish}Now, I must go to prayers. You will join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.88,0:49:30.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 如果大人不介意的话就不来了 - 我们两个都不去\N{\rEnglish}- If my lord will excuse me. - (BRIDA) Us both.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.12,0:49:32.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}当然不介意\N{\rEnglish}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.00,0:49:35.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我早料到了\N{\rEnglish}I expected as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.08,0:49:38.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 贝奥卡神父 - 大人?\N{\rEnglish}- Father Beocca. - (BEOCCA) Lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.52,0:49:41.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 带你的客人去用些茶点 - 遵命, 大人\N{\rEnglish}- Take your guests for refreshments. - I will, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.56,0:49:45.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们可以留在温切斯特, 但我要你负责\N{\rEnglish}They may remain in Winchester, but I hold you responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.32,0:49:47.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是, 大人\N{\rEnglish}Yes, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.64,0:49:54.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你该跟着去祈祷的, 那样能拉近你们的关系\N{\rEnglish}You should've gone along and prayed, it would've bonded you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.56,0:49:55.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他以为我们是异教徒\N{\rEnglish}He believes we are pagans.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.04,0:49:58.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德真正相信的是丹麦人抛弃了你\N{\rEnglish}What Alfred believes is that the Danes abandoned you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.04,0:50:01.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}乌巴抛弃了我们, 但还有别的首领\N{\rEnglish}Ubba has abandoned us, there are other lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.08,0:50:04.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大多数首领, 要不是全部, 都听命于乌巴\N{\rEnglish}Most, if not all, follow Ubba.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.24,0:50:08.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 相信我, 你们已经被抛弃了 - 你觉得你知道关于丹麦人的一切，是吗\N{\rEnglish}- Believe me, you have been abandoned. - You know everything about Danes,don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.28,0:50:10.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这边走, 我有样东西想给你看\N{\rEnglish}(BEOCCA) This way. I wanna show you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.68,0:50:15.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}贝班堡的契约\N{\rEnglish}The Charters of Bebbanburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.92,0:50:20.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 对, 土地登记簿 - 你把它们保住了\N{\rEnglish}- (BEOCCA) Yeah, the land books. Yeah. - You kept them safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.28,0:50:21.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我已经让阿尔弗雷德看过了\N{\rEnglish}I have shown them to Alfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.04,0:50:25.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他知道你才是合法的郡长\N{\rEnglish}He knows you are the ealdorman by right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.80,0:50:29.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我会继续保护他们的安全\N{\rEnglish}I will continue to keep them safe,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.92,0:50:34.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但乌特雷德, 你必须像个郡长那样行事\N{\rEnglish}but, Uhtred, you must behave like an ealdorman.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.60,0:50:47.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那些契约没有任何意义, 诺森布里亚已经是丹麦人的地盘了\N{\rEnglish}The charters have no meaning. Northumbria belongs to the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.24,0:50:49.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}诺森布里亚不属于丹麦人, 是被他们抢走的\N{\rEnglish}(BEOCCA) It does not belong to Danes, it has been stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.04,0:50:53.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你想要财富就去抢, 你不能无视这个事实\N{\rEnglish}(BRIDA) You want wealth, you take it. You can't ignore what's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.28,0:50:55.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果丹麦人在雷丁厄姆, 我就去\N{\rEnglish}If the Danes are at Readingum, I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.52,0:50:57.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 什么? - 去做什么?\N{\rEnglish}- What? - For what purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.48,0:50:58.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去打探消息\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) For knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.96,0:51:01.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们已经有消息了, 你最好离丹麦人远点\N{\rEnglish}(BEOCCA) We have knowledge and you should stay away from the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.36,0:51:04.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去打探新消息, 你们知道他们在哪里安营\N{\rEnglish}For new knowledge. You know where they're settling,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.16,0:51:07.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 但不知道为什么 - 我们知道他们的人数和位置\N{\rEnglish}- but you don't know why. - We know their number and position.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.68,0:51:09.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但不知道他们的意图\N{\rEnglish}Not their intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.48,0:51:11.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我是囚犯吗?\N{\rEnglish}Am I a prisoner?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.00,0:51:14.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们的意图就是进攻\N{\rEnglish}Their intention is to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.88,0:51:16.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}什么时候?\N{\rEnglish}When?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.00,0:51:18.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}春天, 永远都是春天\N{\rEnglish}Spring. It is always spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.68,0:51:21.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我要去雷丁厄姆, 在哪儿?\N{\rEnglish}I'll go to Readingum. Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.20,0:51:23.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 太危险了 - 对我来说不危险\N{\rEnglish}- it's too dangerous. - (UHTRED) Not for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.36,0:51:26.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我是个不信教的丹麦人, 记得吗? - 为什么要替阿尔弗雷德做探子?\N{\rEnglish}- I'm a godless Dane, remember? - (BRIDA) Why spy for Alfred?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.36,0:51:28.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他是英格兰的郡长\N{\rEnglish}He is an ealdorman of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.88,0:51:38.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.28,0:51:40.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人\N{\rEnglish}(BEOCCA) Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.16,0:51:44.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}关于将异教徒改信基督教一事,\N{\rEnglish}Regarding the conversion of the pagans to Christianity,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.36,0:51:48.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 大人? - 我们该如何决定什么才是合宜的做法?\N{\rEnglish}- Yes, lord? - how do we decide what is proper?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.24,0:51:50.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是要启发他们, 还是杀了他们?\N{\rEnglish}To enlighten them or to kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.32,0:51:55.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}传播天主的福音, 当然是我们的使命\N{\rEnglish}Spreading God's word is, of course, our mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.20,0:51:58.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但我担心那些异教徒, 真正的异教徒,\N{\rEnglish}But I fear that the pagans, the true pagans,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.52,0:52:02.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}必须先亲眼见识、亲身感受祂的力量\N{\rEnglish}must first witness and feel his power.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.76,0:52:13.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 乌特雷德会回来? - 是的, 他会回来\N{\rEnglish}- Uhtred will return? - Yes, he will return.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.20,0:52:15.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}是的, 但他会以什么面目回来? 以什么身份? 成了什么人?\N{\rEnglish}Yes, but how will he return? As who? As what?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.76,0:52:18.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我了解这个孩子-- - 但这个孩子如今已是个男人\N{\rEnglish}- I know this boy-- - But this boy is now a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.96,0:52:23.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我了解他的灵魂 - 贝奥卡神父, 他没有灵魂\N{\rEnglish}- I know his soul. - Father Beocca, he has no soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.48,0:52:25.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}而你自己也说过\N{\rEnglish}And you say yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.16,0:52:28.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}那些异教徒需要感受天主的力量\N{\rEnglish}the pagans need to feel the power of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.64,0:52:31.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这就写在这里, 就是现在\N{\rEnglish}It is written, now, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.80,0:52:33.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你退下吧\N{\rEnglish}You may leave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.36,0:52:37.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}且看这几日会带来什么, 大人\N{\rEnglish}We shall see what the days bring, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.20,0:53:02.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}如果他们打算在冬天休整\N{\rEnglish}If resting through the winter was their intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.52,0:53:04.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}就该留在伦敦\N{\rEnglish}they would've remained in Lundene.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.96,0:53:09.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你才是阿尔弗雷德的奸细, 下一步就是替他杀人, 你愿意干吗?\N{\rEnglish}It's you who's AIfred's spy. Next step is to kill for him. Will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.68,0:53:13.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}告诉我, 如果我们渡河去找古思伦, 会发生什么?\N{\rEnglish}Answer me this, if we were to cross and find Guthrum, what would happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.68,0:53:15.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他会把我们都杀了\N{\rEnglish}He'd kill us both.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.32,0:53:16.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我们不欠他们任何东西\N{\rEnglish}We owe them nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.32,0:53:21.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德需要了解丹麦人的情况, 我需要得到他的信任\N{\rEnglish}Alfred needs to know about the Danes, I need his trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.36,0:53:24.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你以为他会把贝班堡交给你, 要是你想错了呢?\N{\rEnglish}(BRIDA) You'd think he'd deliver you Bebbanburg, what if you're wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.24,0:53:46.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德, 你召集贤人会议所为何事?\N{\rEnglish}Alfred, you have called council for what reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.36,0:53:49.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 恕我冒昧, 或许没什么大事, 但有个异教徒\N{\rEnglish}Lord, forgive me, it may be no reason, but we have a pagan
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.60,0:53:51.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}声称掌握有关丹麦军队的情报\N{\rEnglish}who claims knowledge regarding the Dane army.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.84,0:53:53.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 异教徒? - 请恕我冒昧, 大人\N{\rEnglish}- (AETHELRED) Pagan? - Forgive me, lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.44,0:53:57.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他是贝班堡的乌特雷德，我以人格担保他说的话\N{\rEnglish}he is Uhtred of Bebbanburg. I vouch for his word.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.72,0:54:02.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 乌特雷德 - 大人\N{\rEnglish}- (AETHELRED) Uhtred. - Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.84,0:54:08.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我去过雷丁厄姆，亲眼盯着丹麦人看\N{\rEnglish}I've been to Readingum, watched the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.16,0:54:12.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们不是来定居的，要是打算定居，就不会离开伦敦\N{\rEnglish}Their intention is not to settle. If it were, they would've remained in Lundene.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.52,0:54:14.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你的意思是，他们要发起进攻？\N{\rEnglish}You are saying, what, they intend to attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.08,0:54:16.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是的，大人 - 我们知道\N{\rEnglish}- I am, lord. - (ODDA) We know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.60,0:54:19.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 开春他们就会打到门口来 - 用不到开春，就是这几天\N{\rEnglish}- Come spring, they'll be at our door. - (UHTRED) They will be within days.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.64,0:54:21.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我确定 - 你怎么能确定？\N{\rEnglish}- I'm sure. - How can you be sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.68,0:54:23.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 地面还泥泞着—— - 他们已经在祭祀了\N{\rEnglish}- The ground is sodden-- - They made sacrifices.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.12,0:54:26.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}普通士兵捉来寒鸦杀掉祭神\N{\rEnglish}Ordinary warriors caught and killed birds, jackdaws.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.12,0:54:29.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是出战前几天才会做的事\N{\rEnglish}This is done in days before battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.20,0:54:32.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 他们还饿着肚子 - 也许那些鸟就是他们的口粮\N{\rEnglish}- And they are hungry. - Perhaps they have eaten these.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.28,0:54:34.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们人多马多，粮草却很少\N{\rEnglish}They've many men and horses, few supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.64,0:54:37.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}第一步肯定是抢一座粮食和牲畜都充足的城镇\N{\rEnglish}They'll first seize a town rich with grain and livestock.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.84,0:54:40.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这一带我不太熟，但我走过不少地方\N{\rEnglish}I don't know the country well, but I've travelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.64,0:54:42.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我觉得阿宾顿就是这样的地方\N{\rEnglish}I believe Abbendum is such a place.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.88,0:54:47.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}要想打败丹麦人，就得在他们去阿宾顿的路上截住他们\N{\rEnglish}To defeat the Danes, you must meet them on the road to Abbendum.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.08,0:54:49.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人，就是这几天\N{\rEnglish}They'll be within days, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.76,0:54:51.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你一个人去了雷丁厄姆？\N{\rEnglish}(ALFRED) You went to Readingum alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.64,0:54:52.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}和布丽达一起去的\N{\rEnglish}With Brida.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.12,0:54:55.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 为什么单独去？ - 有什么不对吗？\N{\rEnglish}- Why alone? - (UHTRED) Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.92,0:54:58.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}因为你这辈子大半时间都是跟着丹麦人过的\N{\rEnglish}Because for most your life, you lived as a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.56,0:55:01.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你看起来像丹麦人，说话也是丹麦口音\N{\rEnglish}You look like a Dane, you speak the language of a Dane,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.76,0:55:04.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我估摸着，你设陷阱的手段也跟丹麦人一模一样\N{\rEnglish}I surmise you can set a trap like a Dane.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.32,0:55:06.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人说得对，他把我们当寒鸦了\N{\rEnglish}Agreed, my lord, he imagines we are jackdaws.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.88,0:55:08.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}去阿宾顿路上的哪个地方?\N{\rEnglish}(AETHELRED) Where on the road to Abbendum?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.96,0:55:12.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 你会选在哪里迎战? - 就是那个叫阿塞克山岗的地方, 大人\N{\rEnglish}- Where would you choose to meet--? - The place called Asec's Hill, lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.68,0:55:15.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 是你选的还是古思伦选的? - 我亲眼看过, 那里山道狭窄\N{\rEnglish}- You or Guthrum would choose? - I've seen it, the pass narrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.04,0:55:17.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}敌人根本没法包抄我们\N{\rEnglish}You cannot be out-flanked.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.56,0:55:19.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人要仰攻上坡, 那可不好打\N{\rEnglish}For Danes to fight uphill, it'll be difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.12,0:55:22.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}不过他们会很自大, 他们根本不把撒克逊人放在眼里\N{\rEnglish}they'll be confident, they don't fear Saxons.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.60,0:55:25.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为什么? 他们为什么不怕我们?\N{\rEnglish}Why? Why do they not fear us?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.20,0:55:27.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}他们觉得你们不过是一群庄稼汉, 别无长处\N{\rEnglish}They believe you to be farmers, nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.08,0:55:32.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}所以就算阳光正好打在他们眼上, 他们也会往上冲\N{\rEnglish}So even with the sun in their eyes, which is possible, they will climb
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.92,0:55:34.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这对我们反而是个机会\N{\rEnglish}and that can be to our advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.68,0:55:37.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}对我们是个机会, 他说得倒轻巧 你才在这里待了几天\N{\rEnglish}To our advantage, he says. You've been here for days
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.80,0:55:39.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你就说你是威塞克斯人?\N{\rEnglish}and you claim to be of Wessex?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.76,0:55:43.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}简直胡说 这一切来得也太凑巧了, 大人\N{\rEnglish}This is nonsense. This is all far too convenient, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.24,0:55:46.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人, 我的剑是撒克逊人打的, 我这把剑是为威塞克斯而战\N{\rEnglish}My lord, my sword was made by a Saxon. My sword is for Wessex.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.76,0:55:49.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 贵族说话时不得插嘴 - 奥达\N{\rEnglish}- Don't interrupt a noble when speaking. - (AETHELRED) Odda.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.40,0:55:52.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我认为此人和他的话都是冒牌货\N{\rEnglish}I believe this man and this bag of rags to be impostors.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.48,0:55:56.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 没有哪支军队会在入冬之前出征-- - 小奥达, 你够了!\N{\rEnglish}- No army marches as winter approach-- - Young Odda, enough from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.80,0:55:59.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}大人\N{\rEnglish}My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.72,0:56:05.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你\N{\rEnglish}You.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.64,0:56:09.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}你的话给这个会议提供了不少值得商议的内容\N{\rEnglish}You have spoken and given this council much to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.04,0:56:11.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}陛下\N{\rEnglish}(UHTRED) My lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.20,0:56:16.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}阿尔弗雷德, 他是你请来的 现在怎么办?\N{\rEnglish}Alfred, he's here at your invitation. What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.04,0:56:21.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}丹麦人若真的进军, 我们就必须迎战\N{\rEnglish}Should the Danes march, we must face them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.68,0:56:25.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我宁可站在山顶, 也不愿在平地上硬拼\N{\rEnglish}And I would rather be at the top of a hill than on the flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.00,0:56:30.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}我说, 我们向阿塞克山岗进军\N{\rEnglish}I say we march to Asec's Hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.36,0:56:35.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}但把他关起来\N{\rEnglish}But take him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.68,0:56:38.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 把他们两个都关起来，看好了 - 遵命\N{\rEnglish}- Take them both, make them secure. - Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.08,0:56:41.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}这是什么意思? 我说的都是实话\N{\rEnglish}What is this? I have spoken the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.52,0:56:45.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 我说的都是实话,贝奥卡神父 - 大人,求您了\N{\rEnglish}- I have spoken the truth. Father Beocca. - (BEOCCA) My lord, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.88,0:56:50.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}- 贝奥卡,救我!贝奥卡! - 要有信心!\N{\rEnglish}- Beocca, help me! Beocca! - (BEOCCA) Have faith!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.76,0:56:52.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.92,0:57:21.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.32,0:57:36.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}停住!停住!\N{\rEnglish}Hold! Hold!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.44,0:57:44.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}左翼,原地不动\N{\rEnglish}Left flank, hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.64,0:57:46.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}停住!\N{\rEnglish}Hold!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.16,0:57:49.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}弓箭手准备!\N{\rEnglish}Archers ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.44,0:57:51.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.84,0:57:58.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}听我号令\N{\rEnglish}(AETHELRED) On my command.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.80,0:58:03.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\rChinese}为了天主,为了威塞克斯,为了英格兰!\N{\rEnglish}For God, for Wessex, for England!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.48,0:58:05.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
